# Define the directory path
directory_path <- "C:/Users/user/Desktop/GEOHEALTH/OUTPATIENT DATA"
# List all Excel files in the directory
excel_files <- list.files(path = directory_path, pattern = "\\.xlsx$", full.names = TRUE)
# Function to read and standardize a single Excel file
read_and_standardize <- function(file) {
  data <- read_excel(file)
  data <- data %>%
    mutate(
      AGE = as.numeric(gsub("[^0-9]", "", AGE)),  # Clean and convert AGE to numeric
      SEX = as.character(SEX)  # Ensure SEX is character
    )
  return(data)
}
# Function to process files in batches and save each batch to disk
process_and_save_batches <- function(files, batch_size = 5, output_dir = "batches") {
  if (!dir.exists(output_dir)) {
    dir.create(output_dir)
  }
  
  for (i in seq(1, length(files), by = batch_size)) {
    batch_files <- files[i:min(i + batch_size - 1, length(files))]
    batch_data <- map(batch_files, read_and_standardize)
    batch_data_combined <- bind_rows(batch_data)
    saveRDS(batch_data_combined, file.path(output_dir, paste0("batch_", i, ".rds")))
  }
}
# Process the files in batches and save each batch
process_and_save_batches(excel_files, batch_size = 5)

MODEL TRAINING

# Ensure the target variable is a factor
merged_data$DIAGNOSIS <- as.factor(merged_data$DIAGNOSIS)
# Split the dataset into training and testing sets
set.seed(123) # for reproducibility
train_indices <- sample(1:nrow(merged_data), 0.7 * nrow(merged_data))
Train_set <- merged_data[train_indices,]
Test_set <- merged_data[-train_indices,]
# Replace spaces with underscores in column names for both datasets
names(Train_set) <- gsub(" ", "_", names(Train_set))
names(Test_set) <- gsub(" ", "_", names(Test_set))
# Check and align columns
common_cols <- intersect(names(Train_set), names(Test_set))
Train_set <- Train_set[, common_cols]
Test_set <- Test_set[, common_cols]
# Remove the APPOINTMENT.DATE column if it exists
if ("APPOINTMENT.DATE" %in% names(Train_set)) {
  Train_set$APPOINTMENT.DATE <- NULL
}
if ("APPOINTMENT.DATE" %in% names(Test_set)) {
  Test_set$APPOINTMENT.DATE <- NULL
}
# Verify APPOINTMENT.DATE has been removed
print("Train_set columns after removal:")

merged_data$DIAGNOSIS <- as.factor(merged_data$DIAGNOSIS)
# Identify non-continuous variables and convert them to factors
non_continuous_vars <- sapply(Train_set, function(x) !is.numeric(x))
Train_set[non_continuous_vars] <- lapply(Train_set[non_continuous_vars], as.factor)
# Apply ROSE to balance the classes in the training set
Train_set_rose <- ROSE(DIAGNOSIS ~ ., data = Train_set, seed = 123)$data
categorical_vars <- sapply(Train_set_rose, is.factor)
large_categorical_vars <- sapply(Train_set_rose[categorical_vars], function(x) length(unique(x)) > 53)
problematic_vars <- names(Train_set_rose[categorical_vars][large_categorical_vars])
Train_set_rose <- Train_set_rose[, !names(Train_set_rose) %in% problematic_vars]

FEATURE ENGINEERING

# Subset the data to include only the relevant columns
relevant_columns <- c("ConcRT.ug.m3.", "ConcHR.ug.m3.", "AGE", "SEX", "DIAGNOSIS")
subset_data <- merged_data[, relevant_columns]
# Ensure the target variable is a factor
subset_data$DIAGNOSIS <- as.factor(subset_data$DIAGNOSIS)
# Convert all non-numeric columns to factors
for (col in names(subset_data)) {
  if (!is.numeric(subset_data[[col]])) {
    subset_data[[col]] <- as.factor(subset_data[[col]])
  }
}
# Split the dataset into training and testing sets
set.seed(123) # for reproducibility
train_indices <- sample(1:nrow(subset_data), 0.7 * nrow(subset_data))
Train_set <- subset_data[train_indices,]
Test_set <- subset_data[-train_indices,]
# Replace spaces with underscores in column names for both datasets
names(Train_set) <- gsub(" ", "_", names(Train_set))
names(Test_set) <- gsub(" ", "_", names(Test_set))
# Ensure the target variable in the training set is a factor
Train_set$DIAGNOSIS <- as.factor(Train_set$DIAGNOSIS)
Test_set$DIAGNOSIS <- as.factor(Test_set$DIAGNOSIS)
# Apply ROSE to balance the classes in the training set
Train_set_rose <- ROSE(DIAGNOSIS ~ ., data = Train_set, seed = 123)$data
# Ensure factors in the test set have the same levels as in the training set
for (var in names(Test_set)) {
  if (is.factor(Train_set_rose[[var]])) {
    Test_set[[var]] <- factor(Test_set[[var]], levels = levels(Train_set_rose[[var]]))
  }
}
# Train the random forest model on the ROSE-balanced training set
rf_model <- randomForest(DIAGNOSIS ~ ., data = Train_set_rose, ntree = 100)
# Make predictions on the test set
predictions <- predict(rf_model, Test_set)
# Evaluate the model
confusion_matrix <- confusionMatrix(predictions, Test_set$DIAGNOSIS)
print(confusion_matrix)

# Calculate AUC
roc_curve <- roc(Test_set$DIAGNOSIS, as.numeric(probabilities), levels = rev(levels(Test_set$DIAGNOSIS)))
## Setting direction: controls > cases
auc_value <- auc(roc_curve)

# Load necessary libraries
library(randomForest)
library(caret)
# Ensure the target variable is a factor
Train_set$DIAGNOSIS <- as.factor(Train_set$DIAGNOSIS)
Test_set$DIAGNOSIS <- as.factor(Test_set$DIAGNOSIS)
# Define different training set sizes (e.g., percentages of the full dataset)
train_sizes <- seq(0.1, 1.0, by = 0.1)
# Initialize vectors to store results
train_error <- numeric(length(train_sizes))
test_error <- numeric(length(train_sizes))
# Loop through each training set size
for (i in seq_along(train_sizes)) {
  # Determine current training set size
  current_size <- train_sizes[i]
  
  # Calculate number of rows for current training size
  num_rows <- ceiling(current_size * nrow(Train_set))
  
  # Sample indices for training set based on current size
  set.seed(123)  # Ensure reproducibility
  train_indices <- sample(1:nrow(Train_set), num_rows)
  train_subset <- Train_set[train_indices, ]
  
  # Ensure factor levels of DIAGNOSIS are the same in both subsets
  train_subset$DIAGNOSIS <- factor(train_subset$DIAGNOSIS, levels = levels(Train_set$DIAGNOSIS))
  Test_set$DIAGNOSIS <- factor(Test_set$DIAGNOSIS, levels = levels(Train_set$DIAGNOSIS))
  
  # Train Random Forest model on subset
  set.seed(123)  # Reset seed for reproducibility within loop
  rf_model <- randomForest(DIAGNOSIS ~ ., data = train_subset, ntree = 100)
  
  # Predict on training subset and calculate error
  train_predictions <- predict(rf_model, train_subset)
  train_error[i] <- 1 - confusionMatrix(train_predictions, train_subset$DIAGNOSIS)$overall['Accuracy']
  
  # Predict on fixed test set and calculate error
  test_predictions <- predict(rf_model, Test_set)
  test_error[i] <- 1 - confusionMatrix(test_predictions, Test_set$DIAGNOSIS)$overall['Accuracy']
}
# Plot learning curves
plot(train_sizes * 100, train_error, type = "b", col = "blue", pch = 16,
     xlab = "Training Set Size (%)", ylab = "Error Rate",
     main = "Learning Curves for Random Forest Model")
lines(train_sizes * 100, test_error, type = "b", col = "red", pch = 16)
legend("topright", legend = c("Training Error", "Test Error"),
       col = c("blue", "red"), pch = 16, bty = "n")
